description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our experienced and motivated pelvic health physiotherapy team at Imperial College Healthcare NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, well-motivated, friendly and professional individual with excellent organisational and communication skills. The post is part time and you should be able to work within a team but also independently when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will provide support to the pelvic health physiotherapy team and may be required to assist in both the musculoskeletal and hand therapy teams as required. The role will include assisting in the treatment of patients in both an out-patient and in-patient setting (postnatal and gynaecology wards), teaching and carrying out exercise programs with patients both one to one and in a class setting, providing health promotion classes to antenatal patients as well as completing administrative duties. The majority of appointments and classes are currently running virtually. We offer a supportive environment for training and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
